Step-by-step reasoning:

1. The user wants to turn on the Patio Fan-Motor to medium speed.
2. The Patio Fan-Motor accepts the command "On" [DON] with a parameter indicating speed.
3. The "On" command parameter for medium speed is 75 (enum value).
4. Construct the action to send the "On" command with parameter value 75 (unit enum, no unit string needed).
5. No conditions are specified, so this is a direct command.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Set Patio Fan-Motor to Medium Speed",
    "action": {
      "device": "Patio Fan-Motor",
      "command": "On",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "",
          "value": 75,
          "uom": "enum",
          "precision": 0
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
